---
// "Acquisitions & goodwill" — Munger's death-by-indigestion lens. Goodwill is the running tally of what a
// company has paid ABOVE the identifiable value of everything it bought; it grows when it acquires and
// falls only when it concedes it overpaid. So an owner reads the size of the bet (against assets and
// equity), the cash put into buying rather than building, and how much has already been written off — the
// deals already conceded as mistakes. Derivation in lib/acquisitions.mjs; this presents and never grades.
// Withheld when a business grew by building, not buying (its story is told by the other panels).
import { fmtMoney } from "../lib/fundamentals.mjs";
import { acquisitionRecord } from "../lib/acquisitions.mjs";

const { company } = Astro.props;
const $ = (v) => fmtMoney(v, company?.currency || "USD");
const a = acquisitionRecord(company);
const pct = (v, dp = 0) => (v == null ? "—" : `${Math.round(v * 100 * 10 ** dp) / 10 ** dp}%`);
const impYears = a ? a.impByYear.map((x) => x.fy).filter(Boolean) : [];
// Compose the write-down sentence in the frontmatter so spacing is unambiguous, and show the
// "share of acquisition cash" clause ONLY when it's meaningful — when impairments exceed the cash put
// into deals, the deals were largely stock-funded and the ratio (2000%+) misleads rather than informs.
const impCount = impYears.length;
const impSpan = impCount ? `across ${impCount} ${impCount === 1 ? "year" : "years"} (${impYears.join(", ")})` : "";
const shareClause =
  a && a.writtenDownShare != null && a.writtenDownShare >= 0.15 && a.writtenDownShare <= 1
    ? ` That is roughly ${pct(a.writtenDownShare)} of the cash it put into acquisitions over the span.`
    : "";
---

{a ? (
  <section class="acq">
    <div class="head">
      <h3 class="secTitle">Acquisitions &amp; goodwill</h3>
      <span class="srcnote">from the balance sheet &amp; the {a.span}-year cash-flow record</span>
    </div>
    <p class="intro">
      Goodwill is the running record of acquisition risk: the price paid <em>above</em> the identifiable value
      of everything ever bought — a number that only grows when a company acquires and only falls when it
      concedes it overpaid. The size of that bet, the cash put into buying rather than building, and how much
      has already been written off.
    </p>

    <div class="reads">
      <div class="rd">
        <span class="rlab">Goodwill{a.intangibles ? " &amp; intangibles" : ""}</span>
        <span class="rval">{$(a.intangibles ? a.gwPlusInt : a.goodwill)}</span>
        <span class="rnote">{pct(a.intangibles ? a.gwIntPctAssets : a.gwPctAssets)} of all assets — the premium carried on the balance sheet for businesses acquired</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rd">
        <span class="rlab">Against book equity</span>
        <span class="rval">{a.exceedsEquity ? "exceeds it" : a.gwVsEquity != null ? `${pct(a.gwVsEquity)}` : "—"}</span>
        <span class="rnote">
          {a.exceedsEquity
            ? `goodwill alone is larger than the company’s entire book equity${a.equity != null && a.equity <= 0 ? ", which is itself negative" : ""} — strip the acquisition premium and there is no net book worth`
            : `goodwill is this share of book equity; the rest is the company’s own retained and paid-in capital`}
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="rd">
        <span class="rlab">Cash spent acquiring</span>
        <span class="rval">{$(a.cumAcq)}</span>
        <span class="rnote">over {a.span} years buying other businesses{a.cumCapex > 0 ? `, against ${$(a.cumCapex)} of capital spent building` : ""}</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class={a.cumImp > 0 ? "verdict charge" : "verdict clean"}>
      {a.cumImp > 0 ? (
        <p>
          <b>{$(a.cumImp)} written down</b>{" "}{impSpan} — goodwill the company has already conceded it
          overpaid for, charged against earnings.{shareClause} A write-down doesn&rsquo;t cost cash — the cash
          left when the deal was signed — but it is management marking its own past judgement to market.
        </p>
      ) : (
        <p>
          <b>None written down</b> over the record — the goodwill is still carried at full cost. That is the
          deals holding their value on the books so far; whether they keep doing so is the test an owner
          watches, since the write-down, when it comes, is the admission the price was too high.
        </p>
      )}
    </div>

    <p class="foot">
      Goodwill, acquired intangibles and equity from the latest balance sheet; acquisition spend and
      write-downs summed across the {a.span}-year record, from the company's own filings.
    </p>
  </section>
) : null}

<style>
  .acq { margin: 24px 0; }
  .head { display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); padding-bottom: 6px; }
  .secTitle { margin: 0; }
  .srcnote { font-size: 11.5px; letter-spacing: 0.03em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); flex: 0 0 auto; }
  .intro { font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--muted); margin: 9px 0 0; max-width: 74ch; line-height: 1.6; }
  .intro em { font-style: normal; }

  .reads { margin: 16px 0 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(210px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; }
  .rd { border-left: 2px solid var(--rule-strong); padding: 2px 0 2px 11px; }
  .rlab { display: block; font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }
  .rval { display: block; font-size: 19px; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; color: var(--ink); margin: 3px 0; }
  .rnote { display: block; font-size: 11.5px; color: var(--ink-dim); line-height: 1.4; }

  .verdict { margin: 16px 0 0; padding: 11px 14px; font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: 82ch; }
  .verdict p { margin: 0; }
  .verdict b { font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  .verdict.charge { background: var(--warn-tint, var(--accent-tint)); border-left: 2px solid var(--warn, var(--accent)); }
  .verdict.clean { background: var(--accent-tint); border-left: 2px solid var(--accent); }

  .foot { font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--muted); border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); margin-top: 16px; padding-top: 10px; max-width: 78ch; }

  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .reads { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
</style>
